INSERT INTO content (page, section, title, content, image_path) VALUES ('csa', 'main', 'Lycee S t Alexandre Sauli De Muhura Peres Barnabites', 'Lycee S t Alexandre Sauli De Muhura Peres Barnabites Home About Academic Staff Events Announcements Departments Fashion Design (FAD) Accounting ICT Software Development (SOD) Computer Systems & Architecture (CSA) Networking & Internet Technology (NIT) Contact Login Login Computer Systems & Architecture Learn computer hardware, digital systems, and device maintenance. Practical Hardware Labs Students assemble, configure, and troubleshoot computer systems. Future IT Hardware Specialists We train students for careers in hardware engineering and system support. Curriculum Structure Introduction to Computer Architecture Understand basic hardware components, CPU architecture, and data representation. Level 3 Operating Systems Learn OS fundamentals, process management, memory management, and file systems. Level 4 Hardware & Peripherals Study storage devices, input/output systems, buses, and peripheral integration. Level 5 Embedded Systems Explore microcontrollers, sensors, and building simple embedded applications. Level 4 Networked Systems Learn system interconnects, networking basics, and distributed system concepts. Level 5 Capstone Project Apply knowledge to assemble and optimize a complete computer system setup. Level 3 Curriculum Details Level 3 - Introduction to Computer Architecture Basic computer components: CPU, memory, I/O devices Binary and data representation Simple assembly language introduction Mini-project: Assemble a basic computer model View/Download Level 3 NESA Chronogram Level 4 - Operating Systems & Embedded Systems Operating system fundamentals Process scheduling and memory management Introduction to embedded systems and microcontrollers Hardware-software interfacing View/Download Level 4 NESA Chronogram Level 5 - Advanced Systems & Capstone Project Advanced CPU and memory system design Networked systems and distributed computing Embedded systems project development Capstone: Build and optimize a complete computer system Preparation for higher education or IT industry View/Download Level 5 NESA Chronogram About Computer Systems & Architecture Program The CSA program at Lycee de Muhura teaches students how computers work from the ground up. From basic hardware assembly to advanced operating system concepts and embedded systems, students acquire skills to design, analyze, and optimize computer systems for both industry and research applications. All departments Developers IRASUBIZA Jean Cadeau IHIRWE Aimee Saina HABAKUBAHO Brainy Justin TUMURAMYWE Placide Email: lycemuhur@gmail.com School Location Rwanda, Eastern Province Gatsibo District Muhura Sector, Taba Cell Kanyinya Village Follow Us © 2025 LYCEE SAINT ALEXANDRE SAULI DE MUHURA — All Rights Reserved', NULL);
