INSERT INTO content (page, section, title, content, image_path) VALUES ('fad', 'main', 'Lycee S t Alexandre Sauli De Muhura Peres Barnabites', 'Lycee S t Alexandre Sauli De Muhura Peres Barnabites Home About Academic Staff Events Announcements Departments Fashion Design (FAD) Accounting ICT Software Development (SOD) Computer Systems & Architecture (CSA) Networking & Internet Technology (NIT) Contact Login Login Fashion Design Explore creativity through garment design, styling, and modern fashion trends. Creative Workshop Sessions Students learn sketching, fabric selection, tailoring, and sewing techniques. Future Fashion Designers We prepare creative students to work in the fashion and textile industry. Curriculum Structure Introduction to Fashion Design Overview of fashion history, design principles, and creative inspiration. Level 3 Pattern Making & Sewing Learn to create patterns, sew garments, and understand garment construction techniques. Level 4 Textiles & Materials Study fabrics, textures, colors, and materials used in fashion design. Level 5 Fashion Illustration Develop skills in sketching, illustration, and visual communication of designs. Level 3 Accessory & Costume Design Learn to design and produce accessories, footwear, and costume pieces. Level 5 Capstone Project Apply learned skills to design a complete collection or fashion line. Level 4 Curriculum Details Level 3 - Introduction to Fashion Design History of fashion and major designers Design principles and fashion illustration basics Color theory and fabric basics View/Download Level 1 NESA Chronogram Level 4 - Pattern Making & Textiles Advanced sewing techniques and garment construction Pattern making for different clothing types Textile selection and fabric handling View/Download Level 2 NESA Chronogram Level 5 - Fashion Illustration & Accessories Fashion sketching and portfolio development Accessory design: bags, shoes, jewelry Costume and creative project development View/Download Level 3 NESA Chronogram About Fashion Design Program The Fashion Design program at Lycee de Muhura equips students with creativity and technical skills to excel in the fashion industry. From learning sewing and pattern making to developing fashion collections, students gain hands-on experience to pursue careers as designers, stylists, or entrepreneurs in apparel and accessories. All departments Developers IRASUBIZA Jean Cadeau IHIRWE Aimee Saina HABAKUBAHO Brainy Justin TUMURAMYWE Placide Email: lycemuhur@gmail.com School Location Rwanda, Eastern Province Gatsibo District Muhura Sector, Taba Cell Kanyinya Village Follow Us © 2025 LYCEE SAINT ALEXANDRE SAULI DE MUHURA — All Rights Reserved', NULL);
INSERT INTO content (page, section, title, content, image_path) VALUES ('index', 'main', 'Lycee S t Alexandre Sauli De Muhura Peres Barnabites', 'Lycee S t Alexandre Sauli De Muhura Peres Barnabites Home About Academic Staff Events Announcements Departments Fashion Design (FAD) Accounting ICT Software Development (SOD) Computer Systems & Architecture (CSA) Networking & Internet Technology (NIT) Contact Login Login Welcome to Lycee saint Alexandre Sauli De Muhura Barnabites''s School Who We Are Lycee Saint Alexandre Sauli de Muhura is dedicated to forming students academically, spiritually, and morally. Through the guidance of the Barnabite Fathers, we emphasize discipline, excellence, hard work, and Christian values. Strong discipline and character formation. High-quality technical and vocational training. Catholic education rooted in moral and spiritual values. Read More Why Choose Our School? We combine academic excellence, hands-on technical training, and moral formation. Students graduate with solid professional skills and a deep sense of responsibility, leadership, and Christian values. Learn More Technical Excellence Quality training in ICT, Fashion Design, and Accounting. Discipline & Integrity We mold students into confident, disciplined, and responsible citizens. Faith & Moral Formation Daily spiritual guidance from Barnabite Fathers. Programs Our Technical Courses ICT Software Development Software is a collection of programs and instructions that enable a computer to perform specific tasks. It includes system software, which manages the hardware and provides a platform for other programs, and application software, which helps users complete tasks like writing documents, browsing the internet, or playing games. Software is essential because it gives functionality to the computer hardware. ICT Networking and Internet Technology Networking connects computers and devices to share data and resources. The Internet is a global network enabling communication, information access, and online services. Modern technology, including cloud computing, IoT, and AI, relies on these networks to connect people and devices worldwide. ICT Computer System and Architecture A computer system is a combination of hardware and software that processes, stores, and outputs data. Computer architecture refers to how a computer’s components—CPU, memory, input/output devices, and storage—are organized and interact to perform tasks efficiently. It determines the speed, capability, and functionality of a computer. Fashion & Design Fashion Design Fashion Design is the art and practice of creating clothing, accessories, and footwear that are both functional and aesthetically appealing. It combines creativity, style, and technical skills to produce garments that reflect trends, culture, and individual expression. Fashion designers consider fabrics, colors, patterns, and silhouettes to bring their ideas to life. Our Proffesional Course Business Accounting Accounting is the systematic process of recording, summarizing, and analyzing financial transactions of a business or organization. It provides essential information about income, expenses, assets, and liabilities, helping stakeholders make informed financial decisions. Accounting ensures transparency, accuracy, and proper management of resources. Barnabite Fathers School Leadership Providing spiritual, moral, and institutional guidance. ICT Instructors Technical Trainers Specialists in SOD, CSA, and NIT programs. Vocational Trainers FAD & Accounting Professionals preparing students for productive careers. Developers IRASUBIZA Jean Cadeau IHIRWE Aimee Saina HABAKUBAHO Brainy Justin TUMURAMYWE Placide Email: lycemuhur@gmail.com School Location Rwanda, Eastern Province Gatsibo District Muhura Sector, Taba Cell Kanyinya Village Follow Us © 2025 LYCEE SAINT ALEXANDRE SAULI DE MUHURA — All Rights Reserved', NULL);
INSERT INTO content (page, section, title, content, image_path) VALUES ('login', 'main', 'Lycee S t Alexandre Sauli De Muhura Peres Barnabites', 'Lycee S t Alexandre Sauli De Muhura Peres Barnabites Home About Academic Staff Events Announcements Departments Fashion Design (FAD) Accounting ICT Software Development (SOD) Computer Systems & Architecture (CSA) Networking & Internet Technology (NIT) Contact Login Login Access your personalized dashboard by logging in if you are member of staff. Our secure login system allows students, staff, and administrators to manage their profiles, view important updates, track academic progress, and access resources efficiently. Please enter your credentials to continue, and ensure your account information is kept safe at all times Login Username: Password: Login Invalid credentials Developers IRASUBIZA Jean Cadeau IHIRWE Aimee Saina HABAKUBAHO Brainy Justin TUMURAMYWE Placide Email: lycemuhur@gmail.com School Location Rwanda, Eastern Province Gatsibo District Muhura Sector, Taba Cell Kanyinya Village Follow Us © 2025 LYCEE SAINT ALEXANDRE SAULI DE MUHURA — All Rights Reserved', NULL);
INSERT INTO content (page, section, title, content, image_path) VALUES ('nit', 'main', 'Lycee S t Alexandre Sauli De Muhura Peres Barnabites', 'Lycee S t Alexandre Sauli De Muhura Peres Barnabites Home About Academic Staff Events Announcements Departments Fashion Design (FAD) Accounting ICT Software Development (SOD) Computer Systems & Architecture (CSA) Networking & Internet Technology (NIT) Contact Login Login Networking & Internet Technology Learn network design, configuration, troubleshooting and secure connectivity. Hands-on Networking Labs Students work with routers, switches, and real network simulations. Future Network Engineers We prepare students for careers in IT infrastructure and cybersecurity. Curriculum Structure Networking Fundamentals Learn about network types, topologies, protocols, and basic configuration. Level 3 LAN & WAN Technologies Study local and wide area networks, switches, routers, and IP addressing. Level 4 Network Security Implement firewall rules, VPNs, encryption, and secure communication protocols. Level 5 Internet Technologies Learn about DNS, HTTP/HTTPS, cloud networking, and network troubleshooting. Level 4 Wireless & Mobile Networks Study Wi-Fi, mobile network standards, and IoT device connectivity. Level 5 Capstone Project Design and configure a secure network for a simulated organization. Level 3 Curriculum Structure Level 3 - Networking Fundamentals Introduction to networks: LAN, WAN, and topologies OSI and TCP/IP models IP addressing and subnetting basics Capstone mini-project: Set up a simple LAN View/Download Level 3 NESA Chronogram Level 4 - LAN, WAN & Internet Technologies Router & switch configuration DHCP, DNS, and IP routing Introduction to cloud networking Basic network troubleshooting and monitoring View/Download Level 4 NESA Chronogram Level 5 - Advanced Networking & Security Network security: firewalls, VPNs, and encryption Wireless network configuration (Wi-Fi & IoT) Advanced troubleshooting and performance optimization Capstone project: Design a secure network for a medium-sized organization Preparation for professional certifications (e.g., CCNA) View/Download Level 5 NESA Chronogram About Networking & Internet Technology Program The Networking & Internet Technology program at Lycee de Muhura provides a structured learning path from foundational networking concepts to advanced security and cloud technologies. Students gain practical skills configuring networks, troubleshooting issues, and securing communication systems. Graduates are prepared for IT careers or higher studies in networking and cybersecurity. All departments Developers IRASUBIZA Jean Cadeau IHIRWE Aimee Saina HABAKUBAHO Brainy Justin TUMURAMYWE Placide Email: lycemuhur@gmail.com School Location Rwanda, Eastern Province Gatsibo District Muhura Sector, Taba Cell Kanyinya Village Follow Us © 2025 LYCEE SAINT ALEXANDRE SAULI DE MUHURA — All Rights Reserved', NULL);
INSERT INTO content (page, section, title, content, image_path) VALUES ('sod', 'main', 'Lycee S t Alexandre Sauli De Muhura Peres Barnabites', 'Lycee S t Alexandre Sauli De Muhura Peres Barnabites Home About Academic Staff Events Announcements Departments Fashion Design (FAD) Accounting ICT Software Development (SOD) Computer Systems & Architecture (CSA) Networking & Internet Technology (NIT) Contact Login Login Software Development Learn the fundamentals of coding, application development, and software engineering. Students gain hands-on experience creating robust and efficient software solutions for real-world challenges. Software Development Learn the fundamentals of coding, application development, and software engineering. Hands-on Programming Experience Students build real applications and solve real-world challenges. Future Software Engineers We train, empower and prepare students for the tech industry. Curriculum Structure Introduction to Programming Learn Python and Java basics, including syntax, loops, and functions. Level 3 Web Development HTML, CSS, and JavaScript to create interactive and responsive web applications. Level 4 Database Management SQL and database design for storing and retrieving application data efficiently. Level 5 Software Engineering Learn methodologies like Agile, version control, and software lifecycle practices. Level 4 Mobile App Development Create functional mobile apps for Android and iOS platforms. Level 5 Capstone Project Apply all learned skills to develop a real-world software solution. Level 3 Curriculum Structure Level 3 - Introduction to Programming Python basics: variables, loops, functions Java fundamentals: syntax, data types, control structures Basic problem-solving and debugging Capstone mini-project: Build a simple calculator View/Download Level 3 NESA Chronogram Level 4 - Web & Software Development HTML, CSS, and JavaScript for web design Responsive web development using Bootstrap Introduction to software engineering principles Version control using Git and GitHub Agile project management basics View/Download Level 4 NESA Chronogram Level 5 - Advanced Development & Projects Advanced database design and SQL queries Mobile app development for Android & iOS Capstone project: Develop a complete software solution Performance optimization and debugging Preparation for industry deployment or higher education View/Download Level 5 NESA Chronogram About Software Development Program The Software Development program at Lycee de Muhura provides a progressive learning path through levels 3 to 5. Students develop problem-solving skills, gain practical programming experience, and build real-world applications. Our curriculum ensures that graduates are ready to join the tech industry or continue higher studies with confidence. All departments Developers IRASUBIZA Jean Cadeau IHIRWE Aimee Saina HABAKUBAHO Brainy Justin TUMURAMYWE Placide Email: lycemuhur@gmail.com School Location Rwanda, Eastern Province Gatsibo District Muhura Sector, Taba Cell Kanyinya Village Follow Us © 2025 LYCEE SAINT ALEXANDRE SAULI DE MUHURA — All Rights Reserved', NULL);
